{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-classic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/responsive-web-design/basic-css/use-a-css-class-to-style-an-element","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"basic-css","demoType":null,"title":"Koristi CSS Klasu za Stilizovanje Elementa","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Klase su stilovi za visekratnu upotrebu koji se mogu dodati HTML elementima.</p>\n<p>Evo primera CSS deklaracije klase:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&#x3C;style>\n  .blue-text {\n    color: blue;\n  }\n&#x3C;/style>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Mozete videti da smo napravili CSS klasu pod nazivom <code>blue-text</code> unutar <code>&#x3C;style></code> taga. Klasu mozete primeniti na HTML element ovako: <code>&#x3C;h2 class=\"blue-text\">CatPhotoApp&#x3C;/h2></code>. Zapamtite da u CSS <code>style</code> bloku imena klasa pocinju tackom. U HTML <code>class</code> atributu ime klase se pise bez tacke.</p>\n</section>","id":"bad87fee1348bd9aecf08806","hasEditableBoundaries":false,"instructions":"<section id=\"instructions\">\n<p>Unutar svog <code>style</code> elementa promenite <code>h2</code> selektor u <code>.red-text</code> i azurirajte boju sa <code>blue</code> na <code>red</code>.</p>\n<p>Dodelite <code>h2</code> elementu <code>class</code> vrednost <code>red-text</code>.</p>\n</section>","notes":null,"challengeType":0,"helpCategory":"HTML-CSS","videoUrl":"https://scrimba.com/c/c2MvDtV","superBlock":"responsive-web-design","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":18337,"hooks":null,"fields":{"slug":"/learn/responsive-web-design/basic-css/use-a-css-class-to-style-an-element"},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":false,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"indexhtml","ext":"html","name":"index","contents":"<style>\n  h2 {\n    color: blue;\n  }\n</style>\n\n<h2>CatPhotoApp</h2>\n<main>\n  <p>Click here to view more <a href=\"#\">cat photos</a>.</p>\n\n  <a href=\"#\"><img src=\"https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/cat-photo-app/relaxing-cat.jpg\" alt=\"A cute orange cat lying on its back.\"></a>\n\n  <div>\n    <p>Things cats love:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>catnip</li>\n      <li>laser pointers</li>\n      <li>lasagna</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>Top 3 things cats hate:</p>\n    <ol>\n      <li>flea treatment</li>\n      <li>thunder</li>\n      <li>other cats</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n\n  <form action=\"https://freecatphotoapp.com/submit-cat-photo\">\n    <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"indoor-outdoor\" checked> Indoor</label>\n    <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"indoor-outdoor\"> Outdoor</label><br>\n    <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"personality\" checked> Loving</label>\n    <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"personality\"> Lazy</label>\n    <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"personality\"> Energetic</label><br>\n    <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"cat photo URL\" required>\n    <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n  </form>\n</main>","head":null,"tail":null,"editableRegionBoundaries":[],"history":["index.html"]}],"saveSubmissionToDB":null,"tests":[{"text":"<p>Vas <code>h2</code> element treba da bude crven.</p>","testString":"const h2Element = document.querySelector('h2'); \nconst color = window.getComputedStyle(h2Element)['color']; \nassert.strictEqual(color, 'rgb(255, 0, 0)');"},{"text":"<p>Vas <code>h2</code> element treba da ima klasu <code>red-text</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.isTrue(document.querySelector('h2').classList.contains('red-text'));"},{"text":"<p>Vas stylesheet treba da deklarise klasu <code>red-text</code> i postavi njenu boju na <code>red</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.match(__helpers.removeCssComments(code), /\\.red-text\\s*\\{\\s*color\\s*:\\s*red;?\\s*\\}/g);"},{"text":"<p>Ne treba da koristite inline stil poput <code>style=\"color: red\"</code> na svom <code>h2</code> elementu.</p>","testString":"assert.notExists(document.querySelector('h2').getAttribute('style'));"}]}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/responsive-web-design/#basic-css","dashedName":"use-a-css-class-to-style-an-element","certification":"responsive-web-design","disableLoopProtectTests":false,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"responsive-web-design","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"basic-css","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/responsive-web-design/basic-css/style-multiple-elements-with-a-css-class","prevChallengePath":"/learn/responsive-web-design/basic-css/use-css-selectors-to-style-elements","id":"bad87fee1348bd9aecf08806","saveSubmissionToDB":null},"projectPreview":{"challengeData":{"challengeType":0,"challengeFiles":[{"name":"index","ext":"html","contents":"<style>@media (max-width: 350px) {:root {--penguin-size: 200px; --penguin-skin: black;}}</style>","history":["index.html"],"fileKey":"indexhtml"}]}},"id":"/learn/responsive-web-design/basic-css/use-a-css-class-to-style-an-element"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3858520367"],"slicesMap":{}}